\" style=\"text-align:center\"|Diesel engines\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''2.0 TDI CR<br />+ DPF'''||1968&nbsp;cc, [[multi-valve|16v]] [[DOHC]]<br/>[[common rail]]||[[list of Volkswagen Group diesel engines#CAGC|CAGC]]<br /><small>([[Volkswagen EA189 engine|EA189]])</small>||{{convert|88|kW|PS bhp|0|abbr=on|lk=on}}<br />at 4,000 rpm\n|{{convert|290|Nm|0|abbr=on|lk=on}}<br />at 1,750\u20132,500 rpm||10.5<br />sec.||{{convert|204|km/h|1|abbr=on}}||139||09/2009\u2013<br />2013||{{Y}}||{{Y}}||{{N}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''2.0 TDI CR<br />+ DPF'''||1968&nbsp;cc, 16v DOHC<br/>common rail||[[list of Volkswagen Group diesel engines#CAGA|CAGA]]<br /><small>(EA189)</small>||{{convert|105|kW|PS bhp|0|abbr=on}}<br />at 4,200 rpm||{{convert|320|Nm|0|abbr=on}}<br />at 1,750\u20132,500 rpm||9.2<br />sec.||{{convert|214|km/h|1|abbr=on}}||143||12/2008\u2013<br />2013||{{Y}}||{{Y}}||{{Y}}\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|'''2.0 TDI CR<br />+ DPF'''||1968&nbsp;cc, 16v DOHC<br/>common rail||[[list of Volkswagen Group diesel engines#CAHA|CAHA]]<br /><small>(EA189)</small>||{{convert|125|kW|PS bhp|0|abbr=on}}<br />at 4,200 rpm||{{convert|350|Nm|0|abbr=on}}<br />at 1,750\u20132,500 rpm||8.4<br />sec.||{{convert|229|km/h|1|abbr=on}}||153||02/2009\u2013<br />2013||{{N}}||{{Y}}||{{Y}}\n|}\n\n==Other features==\nThe Exeo also features the same multi link fully [[independent suspension|independent]] front and rear [[suspension (vehicle)|suspension]] as used on the Audi A4, again with light weight [[casting|cast]] [[aluminium alloy]] front suspension arms and virtual steering axis uprights.<ref name=AutoBlog/> All models are equipped with [[ZF Friedrichshafen|ZF]]-supplied [[power steering]], with some models having speed sensitive '[[servotronic]]' variable assistance.<ref name=AutoBlog/><ref name=ETKA/>\n\n[[Disc brake]]s are fitted front and rear, with the radially ventilated fronts ranging in diameter from {{convert|280|mm|1}} by {{convert|22|mm|2}} thick, to {{convert|320|mm|1}} by {{convert|30|mm|2}}. At the rear are solid (un ventilated) discs ranging from {{convert|245|mm|1}} by {{convert|10|mm|2}} to {{convert|288|mm|1}} by {{convert|12|mm|2}}. All discs, front and rear, use a single piston sliding brake caliper.<ref name=ETKA/>\n\nChassis electronics feature as standard the [[Robert Bosch GmbH|Bosch]] ESP&nbsp;8.0 [[electronic stability control|Electronic Stability Programme]], which also includes [[anti-lock braking system|Anti lock Braking System]] (ABS), [[electronic brakeforce distribution|Electronic Brakeforce Distribution]] (EBD), and emergency [[Brake Assist]] (BA). This ESP system also includes [[traction control system|Anti Slip Regulation]] (ASR, or traction control), and Electronic Differential Lock (EDL) traction aids.<ref name=AutoBlog/>\n\n[[wheel|Roadwheel]] options vary from a basic 7Jx16 steel wheel with plastic wheel covers, to a number of variants of [[alloy wheel]]s, from 16\" to 18\" in diameter.<ref name=ETKA/> Conventional [[halogen lamp|halogen]] dual bulb (H7 dip and [[H1 Lamp|H1]] main) [[headlamp]]s are standard, with self leveling single source Bi [[xenon arc lamp|Xenon]] [[high-intensity discharge lamp|high-intensity discharge]] (HID) headlights<ref name=AutoBlog/> available as an option.\n\nLuggage capacity in the saloon variant, measured according to the VDA 'block' method, is {{convert|460|L|cuft|1}}.<ref name=AutoBlog/> On the other hand, in the estate Exeo ST variant, the boot size starts from {{convert|442|L|cuft|1}} (or {{convert|564|L|cuft|1}} when loaded up to roof) and after folding rear seats it rises to {{convert|882|L|cuft|1}} (or {{convert|1354|L|cuft|1}} when loaded up to roof with rear seats down).<ref>{{cite web|title=Gama Seat Exeo 2012-precios-ficha t\u00e9cnica|url=http://www.motormundial.es/gama-seat-exeo/|publisher=MotorMundial|date=29 July 2009|accessdate=|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=SEAT Exeo ST. En avant le break|url=http://www.webcarcenter.com/seat/exeo/seat-exeo-st-2009.html|publisher=Webcarcenter|date=2 July 2009|accessdate=|language=French}}</ref>\n\n==Sales and production figures==\nIn the year of 2009, the total annual retail sales number of SEAT Exeo cars was 21,013 vehicles (12,837 units for the Exeo and 8,176 for the Exeo ST version), while the annual production came up to 22,981 cars made in SEAT's plant in Martorell.\n\nThe total production per year of SEAT Exeo and Exeo ST cars is shown in the following table:\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Model || 2008<ref name=\"SEAT Annual report 2009\">{{cite web|url=http://media.seat.com/info2010/annualreport/pantallacompleta.html |title=SEAT Annual report 2009 |publisher=SEAT |date=15 September 2010 |accessdate=15 September 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.volkswagenag.com/vwag/vwcorp/info_center/en/publications/2009/03/GB_2008.-bin.acq/qual-BinaryStorageItem.Single.File/Y_2008_e.pdf |title=Volkswagen AG Annual Report 2008 |publisher=Volkswagen AG |date=7 April 2009 |accessdate=}}</ref> || 2009<ref name=\"SEAT Annual report 2009\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.volkswagenag.com/vwag/vwcorp/info_center/en/publications/2010/03/Annual_Report_2009.-bin.acq/qual-BinaryStorageItem.Single.File/Y_2009_e.pdf |title=Volkswagen AG Annual Report 2009 |publisher=Volkswagen AG |date=22 March 2010 |accessdate=}}</ref> || 2010<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.volkswagenag.com/vwag/vwcorp/info_center/en/publications/2011/03/Volkswagen_AG_Geschaeftsbericht_2010.-bin.acq/qual-BinaryStorageItem.Single.File/GB_2010_e.pdf |title=Volkswagen AG Annual Report 2010 |publisher=Volkswagen AG |date=1 March 2011 |accessdate=}}</ref> || 2011<ref>{{cite web|url=http://annualreport2011.volkswagenag.com/servicepages/downloads/files/entire_vw_ar11.pdf |title=Volkswagen AG Annual Report 2011 |publisher=Volkswagen AG |date=12 March 2012 |accessdate=}}</ref> || 2012<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.volkswagenag.com/content/vwcorp/info_center/en/publications/2013/03/Y_2012_e.bin.html/binarystorageitem/file